<h2 id="what-is-thinkific">🔍 What Is Thinkific?</h2>

Thinkific is an online course platform that lets you build, host, and sell courses from your own branded site. Originally built for creators and educators selling courses to consumers, it's evolved into something more useful for operators: a training infrastructure that scales without flying trainers to every new location.

You upload videos, documents, quizzes, and assignments. Students (or in our case, staff and partners) work through modules at their own pace. You track completion, issue certificates, and enforce prerequisites. The platform handles hosting, delivery, and student management -- you focus on the content.

<h2 id="operator-use-case">👤 The Operator Use Case: Why This Matters</h2>

Most operators don't think of Thinkific as an operations tool. They should.

When I was scaling our WiFi business across thousands of venues, I hit a wall at about location 15. Every new venue deployment required the same training: how the WiFi system works, how to troubleshoot basic issues, how to explain the guest portal to customers, how to read the analytics dashboard. I was either doing this live via video call or sending document packets that nobody read.

Thinkific solved this. I built a partner training program with five modules covering everything a venue manager needs to know. New partners get enrolled automatically (via Zapier from GoHighLevel), complete the training at their own pace, and I can see exactly who has finished and who hasn't -- all before we even schedule the hardware installation.

The result: onboarding time dropped from 3-4 hours of live training per venue to about 45 minutes of review after they complete the self-paced modules. At thousands of venues, that's hundreds of hours saved.

