<h2 id="features">⚙️ Feature Breakdown</h2>

<h3>Course Builder</h3>

The drag-and-drop course builder is clean and intuitive. You can add video lessons (hosted on Thinkific or embedded from YouTube/Vimeo), text content, PDFs, downloadable resources, quizzes, surveys, and assignments. Drip scheduling lets you release modules over time rather than all at once.

For operator training, the quiz feature is particularly valuable. You can require minimum scores before a student progresses to the next module, ensuring comprehension rather than just video watching.

<h3>Student Management</h3>

You see every enrolled student's progress -- which modules they've completed, quiz scores, time spent, and completion status. For multi-location operators, this means you know exactly which venue managers have completed training and which are lagging.

Bulk enrollment lets you add entire teams at once. Group management means you can organize students by location and track completion rates per unit.

<h3>Certificates and Compliance</h3>

Thinkific generates branded certificates upon course completion. For operators with compliance requirements -- food safety, OSHA, industry-specific certifications -- this creates an auditable record of who was trained and when.

Certificate expiration tracking means you can set annual recertification requirements and automatically notify when a team member's certification is expiring.

<h3>Branded Site</h3>

Your training portal lives on your own branded subdomain. It looks like your company's platform, not a third-party tool. For franchise operations where brand consistency matters, this is important -- your franchisees log into your training portal, not thinkific.com.

<h3>Communities</h3>

Thinkific includes a community feature where students can ask questions, share experiences, and interact. For operators running partner networks, this creates a peer support channel that reduces the load on your support team.

