<h2 id="who-its-for">🎯 Who It's For</h2>

<p><strong>Thinkific is right for you if:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>You're onboarding new locations, franchisees, or partners repeatedly</li>
  <li>You need standardized training that scales without your personal time</li>
  <li>Compliance tracking and certification records are important</li>
  <li>You want a branded training portal, not a third-party-looking tool</li>
  <li>You're willing to invest time upfront building courses to save hundreds of hours later</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Look elsewhere if:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>You only need to train a handful of people (just do it live)</li>
  <li>You're primarily selling courses to consumers (Teachable may be a better fit)</li>
  <li>You need advanced LMS features like SCORM compliance (look at enterprise LMS platforms)</li>
  <li>You need mobile-first training for field workers (look at specialized mobile training apps)</li>
</ul>

